<br>
It is really unfair to be a ranger these days in Norrath. I only rant cuz im a lazy fat ass and got nothing better to do.<br>
<br>
Lets compair Paladins/Sk/Ranger and their Parent Class Cleric/Necro/Druid respectively.<br>
<br>
Paladins are the defensive hybrid right? They get the cleric lines of heal/hp buff/ac buff/symbol...They get lower lvl spells of course but still more or less get the good spells and at 59 they get Ressurect or what not (90% rez?)<br>
<br>
Shadow Knights are the offensive hybrid right? (By original theory I think they were meant to be offensive..) Personally I think SKs are the better of the 3 hybrid classes &lt;thus my choice to play one.&gt; Sks get higher AC gear than paladins as far as I checked (i may be wrong with that fancy smancy ToV shit but the quest armor in velious favors Sks correct??). Either way. They get the necros lines of darkness/fear/drain...They get it at much higher lvls but they get it. They also get Feign death, self Dmf, and even Corpse summon.<br>
<br>
Now, we get to the rangers. No offense rangers but when I think group I think Enc/Cleric/War/Shaman/(Rogue/Mage/Monk depending on situation)/SK/Wizard/Ranger/Paladin in that order...in some situations Id take a Ranger &lt;if no Sks or Warriors are there...&gt; but thats my personal opinion. I got nothing against them, i just dislike the fact that my friends lvl 35 warrior has the same HP/AC another friends 50 Ranger...Yes I understand ranger can probably get more aggro with constant snare and they get spells but Id rather have a 50 warrior. Either way, back to the facts. Rangers DO get thorns/heals/regen/snare. Thats not the problem...<br>
<br>
The importance here is:<br>
<br>
For raid situations:<br>
<br>
Necros are useful for DMF/Corpse Summon in raids (maybe some other obscure stuff depending on situation, some necros are good for pulling with the immune crap...)<br>
<br>
Clerics (well yeah, they heal.) are useful cuz obviously heals but also rezzes are good ;p<br>
<br>
Druids are useful for ....hmm...ports out I guess. Maybe an evac =/. Maybe a Death touch? (Old CT)<br>
<br>
well. Shadow Knights got corpse summon &lt;we can use em&gt;, Paladins get rez &lt;we can use em&gt;, Rangers got the ability to take DTs &lt;we used to use them&gt;. But in reality Rangers got screwed out of the only good part of druids for raids in my opinion. Rangers DONT GET PORTS OF ANYKIND...<br>
<br>
I understand in all RP purposes rangers shouldn't port, but should Shadow knights corpse summon or Paladins have a rez (a revive is ok but rez is real good if you think about it). Shouldn't &lt;for gaming purposes and &quot;game balance&quot; more so than RP&gt; rangers get AT LEAST self teleports &lt;gates?&gt;...Give them Tox/WC/BB/DL and they will love EQ (at least I think so). and hell, give them a group teleport...<br>
<br>
The closest thing I can think of to that is Tolans BP? but it sucks to most higher lvl rangers, ToV armor and quest armor is better &lt;at least I think so&gt;.<br>
<br>
Anyone agree/disagree with this?<br>
