<br>
Pulling and positioning with Weaponshield is great.<br>
Velketor is a good example of this.<br>
<br>
Rangers can often also kite adds until chanters get the time to mez em.<br>
<br>
<br>
Every class has its purposes, and so far I havent seen one class that is useless. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ukanyli.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kanyli</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/18/01 10:13:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=598.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ranger's Life isn't Fair (serious read) :*(</span><hr size=1> Hrm.  Frankly, rangers get some of the best druid spells (remember druids are a utility class - so snare, harmony, substitute AC buffs, resist buffs, so forth, though not as strong typically) with the added melee damage and specialty spells.  Track, forage (nothing earthshattering, but very useful), nice archery tricks, root (level 5 druid root is more than enough through the game)...  I've grouped with some  excellent rangers 50+, and will contine to do so.  But those folks know how to play their class, most don't.<br>
<br>
IMHO, they fall behind in heals (compared to paladins), but the druid/shaman healing line compared to clerics is always a tad off.  Seems like rangers should get their heals a bit earlier, but that's just my thought.  Other than that, I actually really like the ranger class.<br>
<br>
Rangers don't suck, people just usually are too thickheaded to see different ways to use them.  No class is cut and dry, and they certainly aren't like every other class.  You want to play a ranger like a warrior, play a warrior.  If you expect druid skills, play a druid.  If you want to twist a bit and come up with new strategies, play a ranger.  <br>
<br>
And, coincidentally, as someone pointed out tonight rangers do get ports.  See, after the rangers complained aboud druids getting ports and not them a nice GM granted them their wish.  Of course, they usually show up naked and can only port to one location, but hey - beggers can't be choosers. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
-Kany <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/utreistaania.showPublicProfile?language=EN>treistaania</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/18/01 10:17:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=598.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmm</span><hr size=1> put a 60sk with epic against a 60ranger with epic and no buffs or spells used only toe to toe and the ranger wins with about 30% to spare...<br>
